<br>
<br>
Was pl'ing my wifes shamen up some today (trying to get her to 51 fairly fast) and went to drop a spiny mace a mob droped on the ground (trash loot) but it landed on her pet instead so i just hit trade.  Well i have other hits on and notice that it was now crushing and not biting, so i handed it a dagger that was laying on the ground from earlier.  The pet was now quad hitting for up to 51 max a hit (level 49 pet btw.)<br>
<br>
So now i was very interested and kill off this pet and /log on.  Made a new pet put no buffs on it and kill 10 dark blue to me mobs with the shamen tanking and the pet attacking from behind the mob.  I then gave it weapons and did 10 more mobs, and finally gave it a Muzzle of Mardo from a mage that was beside me and was interested in it too and killed 10 more mobs (all dark blue to me at 54.)<br>
<br>
Now i know 10 of each is a very small pool to get averages but it did show a pattern.<br>
<br>
No weapons = 8.93 DPS<br>
Weapons = 24.36 DPS<br>
Weapons + muzzle = 29.37 DPS<br>
<br>
So have i just never known that shaman pets could use weapons or is this something new?<br>
